Start from the existing tenant renderer, not from the editor.
Find the page that already fetches tenant data and renders the home page, like frontend/app/(tenant)/tenant/page.tsx.
Keep that rendering logic as the source of truth.
Split the editor into one server entry and one client shell.
page.tsx should do auth and initial fetch.
The client shell should handle interaction only.
Good split:
server: fetch page data, decide selected page
client: edit form, live preview, blur-save, scroll focus
Reuse the same tenant components for preview.
Do not build a fake preview.
Render the same blocks the tenant site uses, just inside a smaller scrollable panel.
That is what makes the editor feel real.
Make the left panel a generated form over the JSON shape.
Walk data and preference recursively.
For objects, render nested sections.
For arrays, render repeated sub-fields.
For primitives, render inputs.
Keep it generic at first.
Make save happen on blur.
On each field change, update local draft state.
On blur, call the save endpoint for that object.
Use a ref or immediate snapshot so the blur request saves the latest value.
Add focus-to-preview linking.
Give each preview section an id.
When the user focuses a form field, scroll the matching preview section into view.
This is what makes the editor feel guided instead of raw.
Add page switching later.
First make one page work fully, like home.
Then fetch GET /api/pages/by-tenant.
Then add a sidebar and page switching.
Add page actions last.
Disable component
Delete page
Refresh sidebar after mutation
Keep the files small.
page.tsx for SSR
HomeEditorShell.tsx for the client layout
HomePreview.tsx for the reused preview
FieldEditor.tsx for recursive form controls
home-utils.ts for path updates and section mapping
Fix routing carefully.
If your frontend has /api/editor/... routes, make sure nothing rewrites them to Nest.
Keep frontend API routes local.
Let only the backend-specific routes go to Nest.
If you want the shortest practical implementation order, do it like this:

SSR page with hardcoded home
live preview using tenant components
recursive form
blur-save
focus scroll
sidebar page switching
disable/delete
If you want, I can turn this into a concrete checklist for your exact files in the repo.